---
// Privacy policy — cookieless Vercel Web Analytics + Speed Insights, local-only theme storage.
// Static page — prerender to HTML served from the CDN (output: 'server' is on-demand by default).
export const prerender = true;
import { css } from 'styled-system/css';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import { SOCIALS } from '../consts';
import { prosePara, proseH2, proseLink } from '../styles/prose';

const para = prosePara;
const h2 = proseH2;
const list = css({ color: 'textMuted', lineHeight: 1.9, pl: '1.25rem', mb: '1rem' });
const link = proseLink;
const strongText = css({ color: 'text' });
const inlineCode = css({ fontFamily: 'mono', fontSize: '0.9em' });

const updated = 'July 8, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How patricksaade.com handles data: cookieless, privacy-friendly analytics and no personal tracking."
>
  <PageHeader breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy' }]} eyebrow="Legal" title="Privacy policy" description={`Last updated: ${updated}`} />

  <p class={para}>
    This site (<strong class={strongText}>patricksaade.com</strong>) is a personal
    blog and portfolio. It is intentionally privacy-respecting: there are no accounts, no
    sign-ups, no advertising, and no third-party tracking or marketing cookies.
  </p>

  <h2 class={h2}>Analytics</h2>
  <p class={para}>
    The site uses <strong class={strongText}>Vercel Web Analytics</strong> and
    <strong class={strongText}>Vercel Speed Insights</strong> — both
    privacy-friendly and <strong class={strongText}>cookieless</strong>. Web
    Analytics records aggregate, anonymized visit data (page views, referrer, approximate
    country, device/browser type); Speed Insights records anonymized page-performance metrics
    (load times and Core Web Vitals). Neither uses cookies, builds advertising profiles, nor
    tracks you across other websites, and <strong class={strongText}>no</strong>
    personally identifiable information is collected or stored. See Vercel's
    <a class={link} href="https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web Analytics</a>
    and
    <a class={link} href="https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Speed Insights</a>
    privacy documentation for details.
  </p>

  <h2 class={h2}>Cookies & local storage</h2>
  <p class={para}>
    This site sets <strong class={strongText}>no cookies</strong>. A handful of small
    interface preferences are saved in your browser's
    <code class={inlineCode}>localStorage</code> instead — for
    example your theme (light/dark mode and chosen color palette per mode), whether you've turned
    on the optional interface sounds, your preferred list/matrix view on the ATT&CK and D3FEND
    maps, and whether the site-wide DFIR sidebar is hidden, collapsed to icons, or expanded, and
    which category it's showing. Those values stay on your device, are never transmitted to a
    server, and you can clear them any time via your browser settings.
  </p>
  <p class={para}>
    The site also registers a <strong class={strongText}>service worker</strong> that
    keeps a local cache of pages and assets (in your browser's Cache Storage) so it loads quickly and
    works offline. That's simply your own copy of this public site — nothing about you is collected
    or sent anywhere. A few other interactive touches — the ⌘K search palette and the tap/hover
    reference cards on terms and tools — fetch a small, public data file from this same site and
    filter it entirely in your browser; nothing is sent anywhere, and nothing is stored. The daily
    <strong class={strongText}>Term of the Day</strong> is chosen when the site is built,
    not computed about you, so there's nothing to fetch or store for it at all.
  </p>
  <p class={para}>
    The interactive tools — the <a class={link} href="/tools/timestamp-converter/">Timestamp
    Decoder</a>, <a class={link} href="/tools/ioc-extractor/">IOC Extractor</a>, and
    <a class={link} href="/tools/hash-calculator/">Hash Calculator</a> — run entirely in your
    browser. Whatever you type or paste into them (timestamps, indicators, files being hashed)
    is never uploaded anywhere; there's no server-side component to send it to.
  </p>

  <h2 class={h2}>Hosting & server logs</h2>
  <p class={para}>
    The site is hosted on <a class={link} href="https://vercel.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vercel</a>,
    which may process standard request data (such as IP address and user-agent) transiently
    to deliver pages and protect against abuse, per
    <a class={link} href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vercel's privacy policy</a>.
    This site's owner does not maintain its own separate logs of visitors.
  </p>

  <h2 class={h2}>External links</h2>
  <p class={para}>
    Posts and pages link to third-party resources (e.g. LinkedIn, GitHub, and tool/vendor
    documentation). Those sites have their own privacy practices, which this policy does not
    cover.
  </p>

  <h2 class={h2}>Your choices</h2>
  <ul class={list}>
    <li>Use your browser's "Do Not Track" / privacy settings — analytics here is already cookieless and anonymous.</li>
    <li>Clear site data / <code class={inlineCode}>localStorage</code> to reset your saved theme preference.</li>
    <li>Block scripts for <code class={inlineCode}>patricksaade.com</code> — the site still renders and reads normally.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class={h2}>Contact</h2>
  <p class={para}>
    Questions about this policy, or want to report a security issue? Reach out via
    <a class={link} href={SOCIALS.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a> or
    <a class={link} href={SOCIALS.github} target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>. Security
    contact details are also published at
    <a class={link} href="/.well-known/security.txt">/.well-known/security.txt</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 class={h2}>Changes</h2>
  <p class={para}>
    This policy may be updated as the site evolves. Material changes will be reflected by the
    "last updated" date above.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
